'''-{zh-tw:永續性;zh-hk:可持續性;zh-cn:可持续性;zh-hant:永續性;zh-cn:可持续性;}-'''（{{lang-en|sustainability}}），也稱'''-{zh-tw:可持續性;zh-hk:永續性;zh-cn:永续性;zh-hant:可持續性;zh-cn:永续性;}-'''，是人們在滿足人類需求與未來發展時，在資源開發、投資方向、技術發展和制度變革中保持環境平衡與和諧的過程<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalfootprints.org/sustainability/|title=What is sustainability|accessdate=2019-05-21|work=www.globalfootprints.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609155223/https://www.globalfootprints.org/sustainability/|archive-date=2019-06-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。永續性可以是一種想法、一種生活系統的性質、一種生產方法或一種生活方式。可持續發展的定義最常見的引述来自[[布倫特蘭委員會|布倫特蘭委員會]]，該委員會是由[[聯合國|聯合國]]在1983年正式召開的世界環境與發展委員會（WCED）。當該委員會成立時，聯合國大會確認，[[環境問題|環境問題]]是全球性的和堅定的，建立[[可持續發展|可持續發展]]政策是所有[[國家|國家]]的共同利益。從這事實看出，在涵蓋所有人類活動的定義，可持續性在界定上部分地方是有困難的<ref>[http://www.worldinbalance.net/agreements/1987-brundtland.php easy-to-read version of] {{Wayback|url=http://www.worldinbalance.net/agreements/1987-brundtland.php |date=20090904154522 }} Our Common Future, Report of the World Commission on Environment and Development, at CWIB. Retrieved, 2008.12.06</ref><ref>[[联合国|United Nations]]. 1987. [http://www.un-documents.net/a42r187.htm Report of the World Commission on Environment and Development] {{Wayback|url=http://www.un-documents.net/a42r187.htm |date=20200422120230 }}, General Assembly Resolution 42/187, 11 December 1987.  Retrieved: 2007-11-14</ref>。有些人認為永續性能夠以環境、經濟與社會三個領域來定義<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Systems View of Life A Unifying Conception of Mind, Matter, and Life|url=http://cosmosandhistory.org/index.php/journal/article/view/503|last=Capra|first=Fritjof|date=2015-10-25|journal=Cosmos and History: The Journal of Natural and Social Philosophy|issue=2|volume=11|pages=242–249–249|language=en|issn=1832-9101|access-date=2019-05-21|archive-date=2020-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201230154146/http://www.cosmosandhistory.org/index.php/journal/article/view/503/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並可考量到文化、技術與政治等子領域<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.academia.edu/9294719/Urban_Sustainability_in_Theory_and_Practice_Circles_of_Sustainability_2015_|language=en|first=Paul|last=James|first2=Liam|last2=Magee|first3=Andy|last3=Scerri|title=Urban Sustainability in Theory and Practice: Circles of Sustainability (2015)|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=|access-date=2019-05-21|archive-date=2017-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626015736/http://www.academia.edu/9294719/Urban_Sustainability_in_Theory_and_Practice_Circles_of_Sustainability_2015_|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Reframing social sustainability reporting: towards an engaged approach|url=https://doi.org/10.1007/s10668-012-9384-2|last=Magee|first=Liam|last2=Scerri|first2=Andy|date=2013-02-01|journal=Environment, Development and Sustainability|issue=1|doi=10.1007/s10668-012-9384-2|volume=15|pages=225–243|language=en|issn=1573-2975|last3=James|first3=Paul|last4=Thom|first4=James A.|last5=Padgham|first5=Lin|last6=Hickmott|first6=Sarah|last7=Deng|first7=Hepu|last8=Cahill|first8=Felicity}}</ref>。根据[[聯合國|聯合國]]在1987年發表的《''[[我們共同的未來|我们共同的未来》]]'' 中，[[可持续发展|永續发展]]被定义为“在不損害後代子孫滿足其自身需求的情况下，滿足當代需求的发展模式” <ref>United Nations General Assembly (1987) [http://www.un-documents.net/wced-ocf.htm ''Report of the World Commission on Environment and Development: Our Common Future''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.un-documents.net/wced-ocf.htm |date=20180113173211 }}. Transmitted to the General Assembly as an Annex to document A/42/427 – Development and International Co-operation: Environment. Retrieved on: 15 February 2009.</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=''Report of the World Commission on Environment and Development: Our Common Future''; Transmitted to the General Assembly as an Annex to document A/42/427 – Development and International Co-operation: Environment; Our Common Future, Chapter 2: Towards Sustainable Development; Paragraph 1|url=http://www.un-documents.net/ocf-02.htm|accessdate=1 March 2010|author=United Nations General Assembly|date=20 March 1987|publisher=[[United_Nations_General_Assembly|United Nations General Assembly]]|archive-date=2020-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420234650/http://www.un-documents.net/ocf-02.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。永續發展可能是永續性的[[组织原则|组织原则]]，但某些人可能將這兩個術語是(視)為矛盾的（即，发展本质上是不可持续的） <ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Oxymoron of Sustainable Development|last=Brown|first=James H.|date=1 October 2015|journal=BioScience|issue=10|doi=10.1093/biosci/biv117|volume=65|pages=1027–1029|subscription=free}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=Sustainability and Sustainable Development|url=http://www.circularecology.com/sustainability-and-sustainable-development.html#.W05THy2ZNBw|accessdate=2018-07-17|work=Circular Ecology|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608194554/http://www.circularecology.com/sustainability-and-sustainable-development.html#.W05THy2ZNBw|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite journal|title=The diverse and contested meanings of sustainable development|last=Williams|first=Colin C|last2=Millington|first2=Andrew C|date=June 2004|journal=The Geographical Journal|issue=2|doi=10.1111/j.0016-7398.2004.00111.x|volume=170|pages=99–104}}</ref>。

永續性一詞的現代用法十分廣泛，很難精確定義 <ref name="Lackey - 1995">{{Cite journal|title=Ecosystem health, biological diversity, and sustainable development: research that makes a difference|url=http://blogs.oregonstate.edu/lackey/files/2017/07/13.-Ecosystem-Health-Biological-Diversity-and-Sustainable-Development.pdf|last=Lackey|first=Robert|date=1995|journal=Renewable Resources Journal|issue=2|volume=13|pages=8–13}}</ref>。最初，永續性意味着僅利用自然可再生资源 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Sustainability Theories|url=https://worldoceanreview.com/en/wor-4/concepts-for-a-better-world/what-is-sustainability/|accessdate=20 June 2019|publisher=World Ocean Review|archive-date=2019-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807124418/https://worldoceanreview.com/en/wor-4/concepts-for-a-better-world/what-is-sustainability/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。永續性從廣義上來講，是能夠保持一定的過程或狀態，但這一詞普遍用於研究[[生態|生態]]和[[社會|社會]]的關係。在生態方面，可持續發展可以被界定為具能力的生態系統，能自我維持一切生態的[[過程|過程]]、{{le|功能 (生物學)|Function_(biology)|功能}}、[[生物多樣性|生物多樣性]]和未來的活力<ref>Regional Ecosystem Office (U.S) [http://www.reo.gov/general/definitions_r-s.htm#S REO Information Center Definitions] {{Wayback|url=http://www.reo.gov/general/definitions_r-s.htm#S |date=20090311091007 }}. {{tsl|en|Northwest Forest Plan|}} (NWFP) definition of sustainability.</ref>。可持續發展已成為一個複雜術語，可以適用於幾乎每一個方面，地球上的生命，特別是許多不同層次的生態環保，包括[[濕地|濕地]]、[[草原|草原]]和[[森林|森林]]，並成為了[[人權|人權]]組織的概念，如[[生態城市|生態城市]]，[[可持續城市|可持續城市]]，和人類活動，如[[永續農業|永續農業]]、[[可持續建築|可持續建築]]<ref>Rita Yi Man Li (2011)[http://onsustainability.cgpublisher.com/product/pub.197/prod.4] {{Wayback|url=http://onsustainability.cgpublisher.com/product/pub.197/prod.4 |date=20171206144249 }}Building Our Sustainable Cities Common Ground Publishing</ref>和[[可再生能源|可再生能源]]。不過，永續發展的字義在某些組織原則中很可能與永續性是相互衝突的<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.circularecology.com/sustainability-and-sustainable-development.html|title=Sustainability and Sustainable Development|accessdate=2019-05-21|work=Circular Ecology|language=en|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608194554/http://www.circularecology.com/sustainability-and-sustainable-development.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The diverse and contested meanings of sustainable development|url=https://rgs-ibg.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.0016-7398.2004.00111.x|last=Williams|first=Colin C|last2=Millington|first2=Andrew C|date=2004-06-01|journal=The Geographical Journal|issue=2|doi=10.1111/j.0016-7398.2004.00111.x|volume=170|pages=99–104|issn=0016-7398|access-date=2019-05-21|archive-date=2020-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200517195158/https://rgs-ibg.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.0016-7398.2004.00111.x|dead-url=no}}</ref>，因為其組織的永續發展可能試圖透過非永續性的方式進行。

[[天然資源|天然資源]]的使用必須控制在一個能夠還原的速度，人類生活才能具有永續性。然而，現在有明確的科學證據表明，人類的生活無法維持，人類需要以集體地減少自然資源的利用，將其消耗速度減少至一個可持續的限度內。<ref>Gismondi, M. (2000). [http://aurora.icaap.org/index.php/aurora/article/view/18/29 Interview of Dr. William Rees] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120530044732/http://aurora.icaap.org/index.php/aurora/article/view/18/29 |date=2012-05-30 }}. ''Aurora Online.''</ref><ref name=MEA>{{cite web |url=http://www.millenniumassessment.org/en/index.aspx |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2008-12-31 |archive-date=2015-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150813135309/http://www.millenniumassessment.org/en/index.aspx |dead-url=no }}Millennium Ecosystem Assessment web site – the full range of reports are available here.</ref>

可持续建筑的理念因此应运而生，它被视为实现城市节能减排、环境保护和可持续发展的重点领域。

== 語源與歷史 ==
可持续性这个名称源自[[拉丁语|拉丁文]]''sustinere'' （ ''tenere'' ，持有； ''sub'' ，在下面）。''Sustain''可以表示“维持”，“支持”，“坚持”或“忍受” <ref>{{OEtymD|sustain}}</ref> <ref>Onions, Charles, T. (ed) (1964). ''The Shorter Oxford English Dictionary''. Oxford: [[Clarendon_Press|Clarendon Press]]. p. 2095.</ref>。永續性的概念，或德语中的Nachhaltigkeit，可以追溯到[[汉斯·卡尔·冯·卡洛维兹|Hans Carl von Carlowitz]] （1645–1714）對於[[林业|林业]]營運的描述 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Hans Carl von Carlowitz and Sustainability|url=http://www.environmentandsociety.org/tools/keywords/hans-carl-von-carlowitz-and-sustainability|accessdate=20 June 2019|work=Environment and Society Portal|archive-date=2019-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111195631/http://www.environmentandsociety.org/tools/keywords/hans-carl-von-carlowitz-and-sustainability|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在人類早期的歷史中，使用火和對特定食物的渴望可能改變了植物和動物群落的自然组成<ref>Scholars, R. (2003). Stories from the Stone Age. Beyond Productions in association with S4C and S4C International. Australian Broadcasting Corporation. Retrieved on: 16 April 2009.</ref>。 在8,000到10,000年前，出現了許多[[農業社會|农业社区]]，這些[[農業社會|社区]]很大程度上與周遭[[自然环境|环境]]建立“永久均衡的結構”<ref>Clarke, W. C. (1977). "The Structure of Permanence: The Relevance of Self-Subsistence Communities for World Ecosystem Management," in ''Subsistence and Survival: Rural Ecology in the Pacific''. Bayliss-Smith, T. and R. Feachem (eds). London: Academic Press, pp. 363–384. {{Doi|10.1016/B978-0-12-083250-7.50017-0}}. {{ISBN|978-0-12-083250-7}}.</ref>。18至19世纪的西方[[第一次工业革命|工业革命充分]]展現了[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]能源的巨大增长潜力。[[煤|煤炭]]曾被用來取代人力與獸力，為效率更高的引擎提供動力，後來又用於發電。在20世纪后期，环境问题已成为全球性的问题。 <ref>D.H. Meadows, D.L. Meadows, J. Randers, and W. Behrens III. (1972). ''[[增长的极限|The Limits to Growth]]''. New York: Universe Books. {{ISBN|0-87663-165-0}}.</ref> <ref name="LPR2008">{{Cite web|title=Living Planet Report|url=http://www.footprintnetwork.org/en/index.php/GFN/page/living_planet_report/|publisher=[[Global_Footprint_Network|Global Footprint Network]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327153856/http://footprintnetwork.org/en/index.php/GFN/page/living_planet_report|archivedate=2009-03-27|access-date=2021-01-23|dead-url=no}}{{Cite report|url=http://assets.panda.org/downloads/living_planet_report_2008.pdf|title=Living Planet Report 2008|date=2008|publisher=[[World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature|World Wide Fund for Nature]], [[Zoological_Society_of_London|Zoological Society of London]], Global Footprint Network|access-date=1 October 2008|archive-date=2011-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716055123/http://assets.panda.org/downloads/living_planet_report_2008.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>  {{Sfnp|Millennium Ecosystem Assessment|2005}} <ref>{{Cite journal|title=A comparison of the Limits to Growth with 30 years of reality|url=http://www.manicore.com/fichiers/Turner_Meadows_vs_historical_data.pdf|last=Turner, G.M.|journal=Global Environmental Change|issue=3|doi=10.1016/j.gloenvcha.2008.05.001|year=2008|volume=18|pages=397–411|access-date=2021-01-23|archive-date=2010-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101125052225/http://manicore.com/fichiers/Turner_Meadows_vs_historical_data.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> 1973年和1979年的[[能源危機|能源危机]]凸顯了國際社會對[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]的重度依賴。在21世纪，全球越來越多的人意識到由砍伐森林和燃燒化石燃料所造成的[[温室效应|温室效应]] <ref>U.S. Department of Commerce. [http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/research/themes/carbon/ Carbon Cycle Science] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DIDNyfJq?url=http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/research/themes/carbon/ |date=20121230083131 |dateformat=iso }}. NOAA [[Earth_System_Research_Laboratory|Earth System Research Laboratory]]. Retrieved on: 14 March 2009</ref> <ref>BBC News (August 2008). [http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_depth/sci_tech/2004/climate_change/default.stm In depth: "Climate Change."] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_depth/sci_tech/2004/climate_change/default.stm |date=20190721074525 }} BBC News, UK. Retrieved on: 14 March 2009</ref>。

== 組成要件 ==
[[File:Sustainable_development-zh-cn.svg|right]]

[[File:Nested_sustainability-v2.svg|thumb]][[2005年世界峰会|2005年社會發展問題世界首腦會議]]確定了[https://futurecity.cw.com.tw/article/1867 永續發展目標] {{Wayback|url=https://futurecity.cw.com.tw/article/1867 |date=20210718173950 }}，例如經濟發展，社會發展和環境保護<ref>[[United_Nations_General_Assembly|United Nations General Assembly]] (2005). [http://data.unaids.org/Topics/UniversalAccess/worldsummitoutcome_resolution_24oct2005_en.pdf 2005 World Summit Outcome] {{Wayback|url=http://data.unaids.org/Topics/UniversalAccess/worldsummitoutcome_resolution_24oct2005_en.pdf |date=20200209052648 }}, Resolution A/60/1, adopted by the General Assembly on 15 September 2005. Retrieved on: 17 February 2009.</ref>。 該觀點已用三个重叠的橢圓表示，表明永續性的三个支柱不是相互排斥的，而是可以相辅相成的<ref>[[Forestry_Commission|Forestry Commission]] of Great Britain. [http://www.forestry.gov.uk/forestry/edik-59fmzf Sustainability] {{Wayback|url=http://www.forestry.gov.uk/forestry/edik-59fmzf |date=20121031192338 }}. Retrieved on: 9 March 2009</ref>。 實際上，这三个支柱是相互依存的，从长远来看，没有其他支柱就不可能存在<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Environmental Sustainability: A Definition for Environmental Professionals|url=http://scholarworks.rit.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1007&context=jes|last=Morelli|first=John|date=2011|journal=Journal of Environmental Sustainability|doi=10.14448/jes.01.0002|volume=1|pages=1–10|subscription=free|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2018-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180731115409/http://scholarworks.rit.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1007&context=jes|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 近年来，這三个支柱已成为眾多[[可持续发展标准和认证|永續性標準和認證]]體系的共同基礎 <ref>Manning, S., Boons, F., Von Hagen, O., Reinecke, J. (2011). [https://ssrn.com/abstract=1752655 "National Contexts Matter: The Co-Evolution of Sustainability Standards in Global Value Chains."] ''Ecological Economics'', Forthcoming.</ref> 。明確提到三个支柱的標準包括[[雨林联盟|雨林联盟]]，[[公平貿易認證|公平贸易]]和[[UTZ认证|UTZ认证]] <ref>SAI Platform 2010. [http://www.saiplatform.org/activities/alias/sustainability-indicators Sustainability Indicators] {{Wayback|url=http://www.saiplatform.org/activities/alias/sustainability-indicators |date=20120131152152 }}. Sustainable Agricultural Initiative. Retrieved on: 4 September 2011.</ref> <ref>Alvarez, G. [http://www.intracen.org/WorkArea/DownloadAsset.aspx?id=51770 Sustainable Agriculture and Value networks] {{Wayback|url=http://www.intracen.org/WorkArea/DownloadAsset.aspx?id=51770 |date=20161018101435 }}. Lausanne, Switzerland: Latitude. Retrieved on: 4 October 2011.</ref>。

永續發展包括在不損及自然環境使其劣化的前提下，滿足本地和全球範圍内人類的基本需求<ref>{{Cite journal|title=What is Sustainable Development? Goals, Indicators, Values, and practice|url=http://www.hks.harvard.edu/sustsci/ists/docs/whatisSD_env_kates_0504.pdf|last=Kates|first=R.|last2=Parris|first2=T.|journal=Environment|issue=3|year=2005|volume=47|pages=8–21|last3=Leiserowitz|first3=A. Harvard|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2017-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710094536/https://www.hks.harvard.edu/sustsci/ists/docs/whatisSD_env_kates_0504.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>[[International_Institute_for_Sustainable_Development|International Institute for Sustainable Development]] (2009). [http://www.iisd.org/sd/ ''What is Sustainable Development''?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.iisd.org/sd/ |date=20130627223823 }}. Retrieved on: 18 February 2009.</ref>。然後，問題就變成了如何表達那些需求與環境之間的關係。2005年的一项研究指出，[[環境正義|環境正義]]与可持续发展同等重要<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Sustainable development (1987–2005): an oxymoron comes of age|url=http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0104-71832006000100004|last=Michael Redclift|journal=Sustainable Development|issue=4|doi=10.1002/sd.281|year=2005|volume=13|pages=212–227|type=Submitted manuscript|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2017-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203074229/http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0104-71832006000100004|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 生态经济学家[[赫尔曼·E·戴利|赫尔曼·戴利]]（ [[赫尔曼·E·戴利|Herman Daly）]]質問到：“没有森林的鋸木廠有什麼用？” <ref name="Daly & Cobb 1989">Daly, H. & J. Cobb (1989). ''For the Common Good: Redirecting the Economy Toward Community, the Environment and a Sustainable Future''. Boston: Beacon Press. {{ISBN|0-8070-4703-1}}.</ref>从这个角度来看，經濟是人類社會的子系统，而社會又是生物圈的子系统。 這種觀點則表示為“环境”内部“社會”内部“經濟”的嵌套圈圖。

健康的生態系统和[[自然环境|环境]]對於人類和其他[[生物|生物]]的生存是必要的，因此永續性與[[環境科學|環境科學]]、[[生態學|生態學]]、[[生物多樣性|生物多樣性]][[環境友善|、环保]][[化学工程|化学工程]]、[[環境資源管理|环境资源管理]]、[[环境保护|环境保护]]和[[人口控制|人口控制]]、[[绿色计算|绿色计算]]、[[绿色化学|绿色化学]]、[[地球科学|地球科学]]、[[环境科学|环境科学]]和[[保育生物學|保护生物学]]等息息相關。另外[[生態經濟學|生态经济学]]研究旨在解决人类经济和自然生態系统的學術研究領域<ref>Bakari, Mohamed El-Kamel (2017). ''The Dilemma of Sustainability in the Age of Globalization: A Quest for a Paradigm of Development''. New York: Lexington Books. {{ISBN|978-1498551397}}</ref>[[生物多樣性|。]]

永續發展在社會層面有許多重要的子議題，涉及[[国际法|国际]]和国家[[法律|法律]]、[[城市规划|城市规划]]和[[运输|运输]]、供應鏈管理、当地和个人[[生活型態|生活方式]]以及[[良知消费|道德消费主义]]。更加可持续的生活方式可以采取多种形式，例如重组生活条件（例如[[生態村|生态村]]、[[生态社区|生态]][[生態村|社区]]和[[生态城市|可持续城市]]）；重新評估經濟部門（[[樸門|永续]][[永續農業|农业]]，[[綠色建築|绿色建筑]]，[[永續農業|可持续农业]]）；利用科学发展新技术（[[環境科技|绿色技术]]，[[可再生能源|可再生能源]]以及可持续的[[第四代反應堆|裂变]]与[[聚变能|聚变能]]）或以靈活和可逆的方式设计系统 <ref name="tandfonline.com">{{Cite journal|title=Flexible strategies for long-term sustainability under uncertainty|last=Fawcett|first=William|last2=Hughes|first2=Martin|date=2012|journal=Building Research|issue=5|doi=10.1080/09613218.2012.702565|volume=40|pages=545–557|last3=Krieg|first3=Hannes|last4=Albrecht|first4=Stefan|last5=Vennström|first5=Anders}}</ref> <ref name="Zhang 2012">{{Cite journal|title=A real options approach to the design and architecture of water supply systems using innovative water technologies under uncertainty|last=Zhang|first=Stephen X.|last2=Babovic|first2=Vladan|date=January 2012|journal=Journal of Hydroinformatics|issue=1|doi=10.2166/hydro.2011.078|volume=14|pages=13–29|subscription=free}}</ref>，並调整個人[[生活型態|生活方式]]以保护自然资源<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Anti-consumption as part of living a sustainable lifestyle: daily practices, contextual motivations and subjective values|last=Black|first=Iain R.|last2=Cherrier|first2=Helene|date=November 2010|journal=Journal of Consumer Behaviour|issue=6|doi=10.1002/cb.337|volume=9|pages=437–453}}</ref>。

